---
import Icon from "./Icon.astro";

const appUrl = "https://app.hideoutbutler.com";
---

<section id="privacy" class="section-divider border-b border-ink-800 bg-ink-950 py-16 sm:py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Privacy &amp; data</h2>
      <p class="section-subheading">
        Hideout Butler uses the official GGG OAuth flow. Your access token never
        reaches the browser.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ul class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <li class="card-pane p-6">
        <div class="mb-3 inline-flex rounded-lg bg-ember-500/10 p-2 text-ember-400">
          <Icon name="shield" class="h-5 w-5" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-parchment-50">OAuth tokens</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-parchment-200/85">
          GGG access tokens are encrypted at rest (AES-GCM) and stored server-side
          only. Sessions use signed httpOnly cookies — no JWT or token in
          JavaScript.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card-pane p-6">
        <div class="mb-3 inline-flex rounded-lg bg-ember-500/10 p-2 text-ember-400">
          <Icon name="refresh" class="h-5 w-5" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-parchment-50">Snapshots, not live sync</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-parchment-200/85">
          Character gear is fetched from GGG on Refresh and stored as snapshots in
          PostgreSQL. Stash snapshots follow the same model when the PoE2 stash
          scope is available. The app does not stream live inventory changes between
          refreshes.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card-pane p-6">
        <div class="mb-3 inline-flex rounded-lg bg-ember-500/10 p-2 text-ember-400">
          <Icon name="link" class="h-5 w-5" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-parchment-50">Public share links</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-parchment-200/85">
          Item and character share URLs are world-readable by design — anyone with
          the link can view that snapshot without logging in. Create links only for
          gear you are comfortable showing; revoke them anytime. Creation is
          rate-limited.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card-pane p-6">
        <div class="mb-3 inline-flex rounded-lg bg-ember-500/10 p-2 text-ember-400">
          <Icon name="globe" class="h-5 w-5" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-parchment-50">Third-party APIs</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-parchment-200/85">
          Pricing may call poe.ninja and the public GGG PoE2 trade JSON API.
          Complements poe.ninja — focused on your own gear and stash snapshots,
          not league-wide economy dashboards.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
